Julius Malema described reports that he had been arrested on Monday morning as absolute nonsense but his driver has been taken into custody.Broadcaster eNCA took to Twitter to post: ? #JuliusMalema and his driver are currently at a police station in the Free State after they were caught speeding this morning. @eNCA had earlier tweeted: #Malema caught speeding on way to court http://ebx.sh/2fOFLl7 while its presenters said they were stopped after being clocked at 187km/h.The Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) leader however himself tweeted: The report that I m arrested for speeding are absolute nonsense I will be at the Bloemfontein Magistrate Court this morning for Land. Free State police spokesperson Nako Ramatso later told eNCA that the driver had been arrested and would be charged while Malema continued to Bloemfromtein. He said the driver had said they were late for a court appearance but Ramatso told him that this would not exonerate them from speeding Malema is to appear for allegedly inciting his supporters to invade land on charges under the Riotous Assemblies Act relating to a statement he made two years ago.Malema told the EFF s elective conference in Bloemfontein in 2014 that: We are going to occupy the unoccupied land because we need the land. For us to eat we must have the land. For us to work we must have the land... I come from Seshego. If there is unoccupied land we will go and occupy the land with my branch. You must go and do the same in the branch where you come from. He recently appeared in the Newcastle Magistrate s Court in KwaZulu-Natal on similar charges. TMG Digital